<div id="sub-main" >
	<div id="wiki-content-block">

	
		


<div id="infobox" class="infobox"> 
 <div class="table-responsive"> 
  <table class="wiki_table"> 
   <tbody> 
    <tr> 
     <th style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"> <h2>Lone Wolf Ashes</h2> </th> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><img src="/file/Elden-Ring/lone_wolf_ashes_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png" alt="lone wolf ashes elden ring wiki guide 200px"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>Type</td> 
     <td><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spirits" href="/Spirits">Spirit Summon</a></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>FP Cost 55</td> 
     <td>HP Cost -</td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td colspan="2"><img title="item_effect_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_effects_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_55px_18px.png" alt="item effects icon elden ring wiki guide 55px 18px" width="18" height="18">Effect 
      <div class="lineleft">
        Summons three lone wolf spirits. 
      </div> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Lone Wolf Ashes</strong> is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spirits" href="/Spirits" target="">Spirit</a> and Summon in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. <strong>Lone Wolf Ashes </strong>summons a pack of three wolves with independent life bars that can move and attack enemies at melee range.</p> 
<p>Despite being called <strong>Lone Wolf</strong>, these ashes spawn <strong>3</strong> wolves that work as a team. Wolves have decent amount of HP, they move quickly enough and they inflict a decent amount of damage. Wolves are better as DPS rather than Tank companions. Wolves are not very useful against <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Bosses" href="/Bosses" target="">Bosses</a> whose attacks have a great AoE. Wolves may not resist many attacks, but they move a lot around enemies, and they dodge a lot, attacking as a team.</p> 
<p><strong>Lone Wolves</strong> can also be found as <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Enemies" href="/Enemies" target="">Enemies</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring" href="/Elden+Ring" target="">Elden Ring</a>. For more information, see <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Lone Wolf" href="/Lone+Wolf" target="">Lone Wolf</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Ashen remains in which spirits yet dwell.<br>Use to summon the spirits of three lone wolves.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Spirits of wolves chased from their pack. They later encountered a nameless Tarnished, who welcomed them as hunting companions. The wolf spirits overwhelm enemies with their agility, aiding the summoner in combat.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Lone Wolf Ashes Location in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The <strong>Lone Wolf Ashes</strong>&nbsp;can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Given to players by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Renna" href="/Renna" target="">Renna</a>&nbsp;at the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Church of Elleh" href="/Church+of+Elleh" target="">Church of Elleh</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Limgrave" href="/Limgrave" target="">Limgrave</a>. Return to the Church after getting the ability to summon your <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spectral Steed Whistle" href="/Spectral+Steed+Whistle" target="">Spectral Steed Whistle</a>&nbsp;from <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Melina" href="/Melina" target="">Melina</a>. You will find Renna sitting by the ruins of the church. [See Lone Wolf Ashes location on the interactive <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=5947&amp;lat=-193.08594&amp;lng=99.207&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=5947&amp;lat=-193.08594&amp;lng=99.207&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">map here</a><span style="color: #828282;">.]</span></li> 
 <li><span style="color: #828282;">If the player missed the opportunity of encountering Renna at the Church of Elleh in Limgrave, the <strong>Lone Wolf Ashes </strong>and the&nbsp; <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spirit Calling Bell" href="/Spirit+Calling+Bell">Spirit Calling Bell</a> can be purchased from the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Twin Maiden Husks" href="/Twin+Maiden+Husks">Twin Maiden Husks</a> in the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Roundtable Hold" href="/Roundtable+Hold">Roundtable Hold</a>.</span></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Lone Wolf Ashes Guide</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Consumes&nbsp;Medium&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring FP" href="/FP" target="">FP</a>&nbsp;(55)</li> 
 <li>They move and attack very fast while in combat</li> 
 <li>They deal high damage.</li> 
 <li>They will often leap backward and forward, destroying the surroundings.</li> 
 <li>They have low health, so it's best to keep enemies entertained while they attack.</li> 
 <li>You must be near a rebirth monument to summon spirits from ashes.</li> 
 <li>When you are close to a rebirth monument and able to summon, a monument icon will appear on the left side of the screen. &nbsp;</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
