				<li id="16724794" class="cmnt-root" data="5" data-d="1656323364000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t576466/Lone-Wolf-Ashes" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">27 Jun 2022 05:49</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16724794" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">a quick heads up for new players about this spirit summons, from first being given them by Ranni to using them with glovewart upgrades in late game areas, they will trivialise a surprising number of boss encounters, from the black knife assassin boss at deathtouched catacombs in limgrave to esgar priest of blood in leyndell catacombs later on, and they take the fun right out of it. I&apos;ve noticed this quite a few times recently, I summon them and the boss ignores me, all three wolves target the boss doing damage as well as staggering them, a full charged R2, a couple of jump attacks or a hit or two from the lion&apos;s claw AoW on great-stars and the boss is done, but it means nothing to me. I didn&apos;t think to deactivate the furlcalling finger remedy before the nox swordstress and nox priest duo boss encounter at sellia town of sorcery, or before the three putrid crystalians at sellia hideaway, I didn&apos;t know I wouldn&apos;t be able to summon any spirit ashes while the finger remedy was active, and I enjoyed those two boss fights more than any when I&apos;ve used the wolves for an easy victory, the putrid crystalians was a tense boss fight, I had to make an effort and it felt especially good when I killed them.</